<subSubSection id="0FF34CCE776FCE80C248415A089CD6BE" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="75F23EB4597097AAA82DF9DDFFC13A7A" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="29D3618074AB10BC3FABD0A65108507E" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">
Differs from 
<taxonomicName id="051548FAFD628B4AA3214A12BA17FB1A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Columnea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Columnea picta" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="picta">
<emphasis id="B91F89150769E1543AC74192E7028D2D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Columnea picta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a nearly tubular corolla (vs. deeply bilabiate corolla). Differs from 
<taxonomicName id="2196B34AA8DE9BEA33B8C6E23304E01A" authorityName="J. L. Clark &amp; Tobar" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Columnea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Columnea angulata" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angulata">
<emphasis id="6688C44C9D4EC3DA3EFBBF7E4C1FFBAD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Columnea angulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the straight corolla relative to the calyx (vs. oblique to perpendicular corolla relative to the calyx). Differs from 
<taxonomicName id="396FCD2DF0A564081AD19A1F80AC41C5" authorityName="J. L. Clark &amp; Clavijo" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Columnea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Columnea tecta" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tecta">
<emphasis id="B3EB4DBE7A4BB7C2313AEA327E175725" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Columnea tecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by corollas that exceed the length of the calyx lobes (vs. corollas that are equal to or less than the length of the calyx lobes).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
